<p>I have a bunch of C# classes, which are auto generated from an XSD. Then I generate XML files based on those C# classes. Nothing existing so far. </p>  <p><strong>The problem:</strong></p>  <p>The generated XML files are going through validation and the validation requires an extra attribute to all XML tags with <code>xsi:nil="true"</code>. Basically the tags should look like :  <code>&lt;testTag.01 xsi:nil="true" NV="123123" /&gt;</code>, but I can't achieve that in C#.  My code is:</p>  <blockquote> <pre><code>     if (myObject.TestTag.HasValue)         {             t.testTag01 = new testTag01();             t.testTag01.Value = myObject.TestTag.Value;         }         //else         //{         //    t.testTag01 = new testTag01();         //    t.testTag01.NV = "123123";//Not Recorded         //} </code></pre> </blockquote>  <p>This code generates <code>&lt;testTag.01&gt;SomeValue&lt;/testTag.01&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;testTag.01 xsi:nil="true"/&gt;</code>. </p>  <p>If I uncomment the <strong>ELSE</strong>, the result would be: <code>&lt;testTag.01&gt;SomeValue&lt;/testTag.01&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;testTag.01 NV="123123" /&gt;</code>. </p>  <p>So I have no idea how to get to the format, which is required by the validation tool. Any ideas ?</p>